BEGIN_TEXT
Suppose \(Z_t\) is white noise with mean zero. After suitable pre-processing, the monthly sales of a consumer product was modelled by the process 
 \[ X_t = $alpha X_{t-1} + Z_t + $beta Z_{t-1}. \]
Five years of monthly observations were used in fitting the above model, the most recent observation being $dat and the corresponding fitted value being $dat_est. The estimate of the standard deviation of \(Z_t\) is found to be $sigma. Provide answers to the following to three decimal places.

